name: Wes S
text:
Update:  Store is permanently closed.
Store converted to a closeout center in early 2017 and is now scheduled to close as of Sept 2017.  As of then, it only had a few items, all of which were 70% off.  Very slim selection though.

name: Kyle Brown
text: Awesome place. They have an outlet section in the back great deals. Very friendly staff and helpfull.

name: Brad Exum
text: Small selection but the customer service was great! If you want to get high quality gear for hiking it's a great place to start!

name: Orrin Daugherty
text: Decent priced clothes and many styles from high end to everyday wear

name: Matt Estes
text: Good atmosphere, not a bad selection, and excellent customer service. Recommended!

name: Rachel Evjen
text: For an outlet store, their prices are a little high. They markup the knock offs just as high as the originals

name: Brad Blackburn
text: Good prices on clothes

name: Ian Houle
text: Great place to learn great life skills

name: Betty Godwin
text: The camp ranger is very kind and the property was very clean.

text: Lots of trails and hiking. Love the views.

name: Mike Martin
text: Love this camp!!

name: Paul Roberts
text: Great!

name: Drew Hill
text: Super helpful and friendly staff. Stop on by for all your scouting apparel needs

name: Wes S
text: This location gets 4 stars because the ladies who work there are very helpful and friendly.  Most of their items are overpriced, however, and my one complaint about the ladies is that they always try to sell new cub scouts things like pants, hats, and even socks.  No one around here wears anything but the shirt and neckerchief and they know it.

name: David McCaughtry
text: Great people... Great program

name: Stuart Bear
text: Great place for scout stuff and CAMPING GEAR !

name: Winston Jordan
text: Great people, great organization, couldn't ask for anything better

name: Dylan Theg
text: Great staff, good selection, and good layout

name: William Cox
text: Wonderful employees.

name: David and Crystal
text: Great place

name: Laura Humphrey
text: My heart has been here for over 20 years. I finally got to do something that not many people get to do. It is beautiful and precious to me. Respect this land.

name: Rodney Hopkins
text: Nice lol get away good riding trails.

name: tyen hoff
text: They lady was nice and tried to help

name: Ellen George
text: The trail to Mystic Falls is closed to the public.  It seems that guests to the equestrian park are now the only ones who can visit. There is a gate and numerous no trespassing signs on the trailhead. Do not come here if you are looking to visit the waterfall.

name: Linda Joyner
text: Great technical trails and good facility for camping with horses. Trails can be a bit eroded at times, but the scenery is second to none in Alabama!

name: Richard Skelton
text: Very friendly people .BEAUTIFUL place

name: Norman Hunter
text: Great trails for endurance rides.  Staff was excellent.

name: melody lecroix
text: Really well set up

name: Gabriel Marrero
text: This store is the BEST Mountain High I’ve been to. They have everything in stock and the have the best service ever! Michael, Lauren and Laura are just fantastic people to deal with! Please visit them and sponsor our neighborhood businesses!

name: MDA
text: Good outfitter. Lots of  clothes. Could use a bit more gear.

name: Julie Ritchey Miles
text: variety of clothingg shoes but. Pricey my. Daughter loved it

name: Dan Watson
text: Great store very knowledgeable, friendly & helpful staff. Bought my Osprey 28ltr day pack there and couldn’t be happier. Go see them you want be disappointed tell um Dirtdog sent you.

name: Ylia Wilson
text: Wonderful store. Super service. Michael is just the best!

name: Danish Pockets
text: I work here so...yeah

name: Dwayne Hodges
text: It is a good place

name: Ron Perkins
text: Great people and beautiful location. Sprawling facility that is a great place to shoot a fun and challenging round of clays or five stand. They've got some nice shotguns and gear in the store. Everything needed for clays and even fly fishing. We had a corporate event there and I went back to shoot with the family. Incredible service every time!

name: Greg Cawthon
text: My wife and I had a amazing time there. I’ve shot before, but my wife had never done this before. Recommend highly if you are a beginner, don’t let the facility intimidate you. Great course, even better people. Steve was our gunner/trapper and he was very patient and made the experience better than expected. Wil definitely be back.

name: Kathy Chesser
text:
Our company had a clay shoot benefiting Children’s of Ala. and we were extremely please with all that ORVIS did for our customers during the event. Our customers had a great time & said the staff was extremely helpful. I appreciated all the special service they gave to or customers and for Thomas Oil company in raising money for Children’s.  We look forward to next year!
Thank you ORVIS!

name: Court Rose
text: Had the opportunity to do some shooting this pass Saturday,  we had Jim, such a great guy! we all had a blast,  your friends from the kubota group,

name: Chace Hatcher
text: Nice course all around fun

name: Michael Stanfield
text: There was this guy named Carl who was the most helpful attendant of anywhere I have ever shopped. I will come back because of his great service! He will set you up withe best outdoor clothing and equipment

name: Christina Morgan
text: Great selection of certain brands. Helpful staff (although they all appear to be teens with not much experience actually using  the products beyond fashion), willing to do what they can to find what you need from any store. I like supporting more local businesses, so this place is great. Clean, well organized, and decent stock. We shop there a lot.

resp.text: Thank you for being such loyal customers! We appreciate it!

name: Kenneth Baker
text: The staff was nice as we were looking around while waiting on our kids.

name: Jeanna Lang
text: Great local outdoor shop, very helpful employees. Decent selection of climbing gear.

name: Mitchell Hunter
text: The team here was super helpful and had the products I needed(down detergent). The guy who helped me locate it in the store hadn't heard of it and asked if I had any tips for washing down jackets. Love the fact that they aren't pretentious and act like they know it all. Helpful and always looking to learn. Love it!

name: Will Delong
text: I was able to find some great gifts for my nephew here who is big into fishing. I picked up a few clothes items for myself. The stuff is high quality and you can tell it will last.

name: Timmy G
text: Staff was super helpful and knowledgeable of products! Thank you for making shopping experience fast and easy!

name: Bill Clarke
text: Called before driving to see if they had hiking trail maps for North AL....they said they did.  What a waste of time....do not believe what the manager tells you...wasted my time and gas.  Instead drove to Mountain High Outfitters....called them also and they told the truth and indeed had the maps and were very helpful.  Would say don't waste your time with Alabama Outdoors!!

resp.text: Hi Bill! I'm sorry you had such a bad experience. We'd love to have a change to ear back your business, and know how we could improve in the future. Please email marketing@aloutdoors.com if you'd like to talk.

name: Ace and Bear
text: We have enjoyed shopping here. The customer service is always top knotch and they offer quality clothing.

name: TrailSlug
text: Very good selection of outdoor gear.   The employees are very helpful and friendly.

name: I'm out
text: Real life hiking supplies. It's just what you need.

name: Emily Rogers
text: Great shop with outdoorsy finds and local swag.

resp.text: Thank you so much for shopping with us!

name: Personal Gmail Acct Alabama
text: Overpriced but all outdoor stores that aren't like REI are. Cool local themed stuff

resp.text: Thanks for shopping with us! Please consider subscribing to our email to find out about our sales and new local merchandise!

text: Pretty darn good selection although their prices are a bit high. That's okay, except the store itself is pretty small so they don't have room for cheapo gear which would be kind of nice.
